  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "15:26,27. The blessed Spirit will maintain the cause of Christ in the world, notwithstanding the opposition it meets with. Believers taught and encouraged by his influences, would bear testimony to Christ and his salvation.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ye also shall bear witness - You shall be witnesses to the world to urge on them the evidences that the Lord Jesus is the Messiah.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Have been with me - They had for more than three years seen his works, and were therefore qualified to bear witness of his character and doctrines.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "From the beginning - From his entrance on the public work of the ministry, Matthew 4:17-22. Compare Acts 1:21-22. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "From the beginning - From his entrance on the public work of the ministry, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 4:17-22",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Compare ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Acts 1:21-22",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "27. ye also shall bear witness—rather, \"are witnesses\"; with reference indeed to their future witness-bearing, but putting the emphasis upon their present ample opportunities for acquiring their qualifications for that great office, inasmuch as they had been \"with Him from the beginning.\" (See on [1865]Lu 1:2).   ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " He adds also, they should testify, &c.: the apostles, and their successors, by the preaching of the gospel; but particularly the apostles, ",
        "children": []
